## Treasury Terminology Reference

### Fiscal Year
- **FY2024** = October 1, 2023 through September 30, 2024. September bulletins typically have full fiscal year summaries.

### Budget Terms

| Term | Definition |
|------|------------|
| **Receipts** | Total government revenue (taxes, fees, etc.) |
| **Outlays** | Total government spending |
| **Surplus** | Receipts > Outlays (positive balance) |
| **Deficit** | Receipts < Outlays (negative balance) |
| **Nominal dollars** | Face value, not adjusted for inflation. Same as "current dollars." |
| **Real dollars** | Adjusted for inflation (constant purchasing power). Explicitly noted when used. |

### ESF Balance Sheet Structure

| Term | Definition |
|------|------------|
| **Capital account** | Original $2B appropriated minus $1.8B transferred to IMF = ~$200M (fixed) |
| **Net income (loss)** | Cumulative profits/losses from SDR and forex operations |
| **Total capital** | Capital account + Net income (loss) — **THIS is "total capital held"** |
| **Total liabilities** | SDR certificates + SDR allocations + other liabilities |
| **Total liabilities and capital** | Sum of all liabilities plus total capital |

### Common Table Types

| Table | Content |
|-------|---------|
| ESF-1 | Balance sheet (assets, liabilities, capital) |
| ESF-2 | Income and expense statement |
| FFO-1 | Receipts and outlays |
| FD-1, FD-2 | Public/Federal debt |
| FD-4, FD-5 | Interest rates, T-bill rates |

